      "text": "CYLINDER BLOCK"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Inspection (Cont'd)"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "procedure",
      "id": "cylinder_block_inspection_contd",
      "title": "Cylinder Block Inspection (Continued)",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 5,
          "text": "Determine piston oversize according to amount of cylinder wear.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": [
            "Oversize pistons are available for service. Refer to S.D.S."
          ]
        },
        {
          "step": 6,
          "text": "Cylinder bore size is determined by adding piston-to-bore clearance to piston diameter \"A\".\nRebored size calculation:\nD = A + B - C\nwhere,\nD: Bored diameter\nA: Piston diameter as measured\nB: Piston-to-bore clearance\nC: Honing allowance 0.02 mm (0.0008 in)",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 7,
          "text": "Install main bearing caps, and tighten to the specified torque to prevent distortion of cylinder bores in final assembly.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 8,
          "text": "Cut cylinder bores.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": [
            "When any cylinder needs boring, all other cylinders must also be bored.",
            "Ensure that boring machines instructions are closely followed."
          ]
        },
        {
          "step": 9,
          "text": "Hone cylinders to obtain specified piston-to-bore clearance.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 10,
          "text": "Measure finished cylinder bore for out-of-round and taper.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": [
            "Measurement should be done after cylinder bore cools down."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "CRANKSHAFT"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "procedure",
      "id": "crankshaft_inspection",
      "title": "Crankshaft Inspection",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 1,
          "text": "Check crankshaft main and pin journals for score, wear or cracks.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 2,
          "text": "With a micrometer, measure journals for taper and out-of-round.",
          "figure_ref": "fig1",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 3,
          "text": "Measure crankshaft runout.",
          "figure_ref": "fig2",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        }
      ]
    },
